!!【柯林斯英汉双解大词典】

:<div>

gesture /ˈdʒɛstʃə/

(gesturing,gestured,gestures) 

1. N-COUNT A gesture is a movement that you make with a part of your body, especially your hands, to express emotion or information. 手势 

例： Sarah made a menacing gesture with her fist. 萨拉用拳头做了个威胁的手势。 

2. N-COUNT A gesture is something that you say or do in order to express your attitude or intentions, often something that you know will not have much effect. 姿态; 表示 

例： He questioned the government's commitment to peace and called on it to make a gesture of good will. 他质疑政府的和平承诺，并呼吁其摆出善意姿态。 

3. V-I If you gesture , you use movements of your hands or head in order to tell someone something or draw their attention to something. 打手势; 用动作示意 

例： I gestured toward the boathouse, and he looked inside. 我朝停船小屋打手势，他在里面看了看。

